
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    `gnome-terminal.real` barnameye asli baraye baz kardan terminal dar muhit GNOME ast. Ba estefade az in barname, shoma mitavanid dastoorat UNIX/Linux ra vared konid va ejra konid. In barname be shoma yek panjareh terminal ba ghabeliat-haie mesle tab-bandi va profile-bandi midahad.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `--profile <esm-profile>` --> 👤 Baz kardan terminal ba yek profile khass. Profile-ha mesle tem-ha hastand va rang-ha, font-ha va raftare terminal ra taeen mikonand.
    🔹 `--tab`                 --> ➕ Baz kardan tab jadid dar haman panjare terminal.
    🔹 `--window`              --> 🔲 Baz kardan yek panjare terminal jadid.
    🔹 `-e`, `--command <dastoor>`  --> 🚀 Ejra kardan dastoor khass dar terminal.
    🔹 `--title <unvan>`       --> 🏷️ Taaeen unvan baraye panjare terminal.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ gnome-terminal.real

    🔹 Baz kardan yek panjare terminal sade.

    $ gnome-terminal.real --tab -e "top"

    🔹 Baz kardan yek tab jadid va ejra kardan dastoor "top" dar aan.

    $ gnome-terminal.real --window --title="My Server" -e "ssh user@server"

    🔹 Baz kardan yek panjare terminal jadid ba unvan "My Server" va etesal be yek server SSH.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ gnome-terminal.real --profile="Dark"

    🔹 Terminal ba profile "Dark" baz mishavad, ke rang-ha va font-haye tire darad. In baraye estefade dar shab munasib ast.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    `gnome-terminal.real` is the actual program used to launch the terminal in the GNOME desktop environment. It allows you to enter and execute UNIX/Linux commands. It provides a terminal window with features such as tabs and profile management.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `--profile <profile-name>` --> 👤 Open the terminal with a specific profile. Profiles are like themes that define the colors, fonts, and behavior of the terminal.
    🔹 `--tab`                 --> ➕ Open a new tab within the same terminal window.
    🔹 `--window`              --> 🔲 Open a new terminal window.
    🔹 `-e`, `--command <command>`  --> 🚀 Execute a specific command in the terminal.
    🔹 `--title <title>`       --> 🏷️ Set the title for the terminal window.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ gnome-terminal.real

    🔹 Open a basic terminal window.

    $ gnome-terminal.real --tab -e "top"

    🔹 Open a new tab and execute the "top" command in it.

    $ gnome-terminal.real --window --title="My Server" -e "ssh user@server"

    🔹 Open a new terminal window with the title "My Server" and connect to an SSH server.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ gnome-terminal.real --profile="Dark"

    🔹 The terminal will open with the "Dark" profile, which has dark colors and fonts. This is suitable for use at night.
